vi.welcome: Chào mừng các bạn\nđến với game

en.quote1: "Don't cry because it's over, smile because it happened."\n- Dr. Seuss -
en.quote2: "You only live once, but if you do it right, once is enough."\n- Mae West -
en.quote3: "In three words I can sum up everything I've learned about life: it goes on."\n- Robert Frost -
en.quote4: "To live is the rarest thing in the world. Most people exist, that is all."\n- Oscar Wilde -
en.quote5: "It is better to be hated for what you are than to be loved for what you are not."\n- André Gide -
en.quote6: "Life is what happens to you while you're busy making other plans."\n- Allen Saunders -
en.quote7: "Sometimes the questions are complicated and the answers are simple."\n- Dr. Seuss -
en.quote8: "I'm not afraid of death; I just don't want to be there when it happens."\n- Woody Allen -
en.quote9: "Everything you can imagine is real."\n- Pablo Picasso -
en.quote10: "Life is like riding a bicycle. To keep your balance, you must keep moving."\n- Albert Einstein -
en.quote11: "Life isn't about finding yourself. Life is about creating yourself."\n- George Bernard Shaw -
en.quote12: "I'm the one that's got to die when it's time for me to die, so let me live my life the way I want to."\n- Jimi Hendrix -
en.quote13: "Just when you think it can't get any worse, it can. And just when you think it can't get any better, it can."\n- Nicholas Sparks -
en.quote14: "Things change. And friends leave. Life doesn't stop for anybody."\n- Stephen Chbosky -
en.quote15: "The fear of death follows from the fear of life. A man who lives fully is prepared to die at any time."\n- Mark Twain -
en.quote16: "The one you love and the one who loves you are never, ever the same person."\n- Chuck Palahniuk -
en.quote17: "If you don't know where you're going, any road'll take you there"\n- George Harrison -
en.quote18: "We are what we pretend to be, so we must be careful about what we pretend to be."\n- Kurt Vonnegut -
en.quote19: "Some infinities are bigger than other infinities."\n- John Green -
en.quote20: "Life's hard. It's even harder when you're stupid."\n- John Wayne -
en.quote21: "Death ends a life, not a relationship."\n- Mitch Albom -
en.quote22: "Fear is a part of life, if you live, you fear."\n- Diablo 3 -
en.quote23: "Where there is love there is life."\n- Mahatma Gandhi -
en.quote24: "You cannot find peace by avoiding life."\n- Virginia Woolf -
en.quote25: "We have to dare to be ourselves, however frightening or strange that self may prove to be."\n- May Sarton -
en.quote26: "Anyone who lives within their means suffers from a lack of imagination."\n- Oscar Wilde -
en.quote27: "Get busy living or get busy dying."\n- Stephen King -
en.quote28: "May you live every day of your life."\n- Jonathan Swift -
en.quote29: "Life can only be understood backwards; but it must be lived forwards."\n- Søren Kierkegaard -
en.quote30: "Do not go where the path may lead, go instead where there is no path and leave a trail."\n- Ralph Waldo Emerson -
en.quote31: "If my life is going to mean anything, I have to live it myself."\n- Rick Riordan -
en.quote32: "It is said that your life flashes before your eyes just before you die. That is true, it's called Life."\n- Terry Pratchett -
en.quote33: "Life is to be enjoyed, not endured"\n- Gordon B. Hinckley -
en.quote34: "Tell the truth, or someone will tell it for you."\n- Stephanie Klein -
en.quote35: "Monsters are real, and ghosts are real too. They live inside us, and sometimes, they win."\n- Stephen King -
en.quote36: "The more I see, the less I know for sure."\n- John Lennon -
en.quote37: "If I can stop one heart from breaking, I shall not live in vain."\n- Emily Dickinson -
en.quote38: "The most wasted of all days is one without laughter."\n- E.E. Cummings -
en.quote39: "Unbeing dead isn't being alive."\n- E.E. Cummings -
en.quote40: "Some people have lives; some people have music."\n- John Green -
en.quote41: "This is your life and its ending one moment at a time."\n- Chuck Palahniuk -
en.quote42: "I've got nothing to do today but smile."\n- Paul Simon -
en.quote43: "That it will never come again is what makes life so sweet."\n- Emily Dickinson -
en.quote44: "Do I not destroy my enemies when I make them my friends?"\n- Abraham Lincoln -
en.quote45: "No persons are more frequently wrong, than those who will not admit they are wrong."\n- François de La Rochefoucauld -
en.quote46: "Life is a book and there are a thousand pages I have not yet read."\n- Cassandra Clare -
en.quote47: "I don't like people who have never fallen or stumbled"\n- Boris Pasternak -
en.quote48: "The past has no power over the present moment."\n- Eckhart Tolle -
en.quote49: "The trouble is if you don’t spend your life yourself, other people spend it for you."\n- Peter Shaffer -
en.quote50: "There's nowhere you can be that isn't where you're meant to be..."\n- John Lennon -
en.quote51: "You can have it all. Just not all at once."\n- Oprah Winfrey -
en.quote52: "I'll try anything once, twice if I like it, three times to make sure."\n- Mae West -
